    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yes, more than it being CommonJS, it's written in a way that doesn't allow for tree shaking, with a single class being in charge of all functionality. We have future plans of changing that, but it's very complicated (lots of legacy code in that part).\r\n\r\nGlad tree shaking isn't broken!",
